Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.02,1:27:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,get a white one.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.02,1:27:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so out of the sameness of that 190, conventional thinkingness of the 20 line,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.09,1:28:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego which prevailed, suddenly it's almost like it gets dissatisfied with itself and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.15,1:28:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it jumps itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.56,1:28:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know, just we could say mathematically speaking, from the viewpoint of chaos theory,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.32,1:28:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you could predict that if the consciousness of mankind stays at 190 century after century,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.58,1:28:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if you project far enough ahead in time, suddenly it will jump beyond 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.68,1:28:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is, if the human conscience is raising up 204.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.38,1:28:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.38,1:28:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to be quite courageous in a way, because in a common sense, the pessimistic
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.04,1:28:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,view seems to be getting more stronger somehow.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.54,1:28:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.54,1:28:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the pessimistic view is not really stronger.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.32,1:28:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always been there.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.09,1:28:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's always the naysayers.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.19,1:28:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always the people that predict there's going to be more people on the planet than
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.65,1:28:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the planet can supply food, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.76,1:28:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it extrapolates into the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.62,1:29:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is in the present, which is an error.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.26,1:29:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a scientific error.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.64,1:29:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mathematical error.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.66,1:29:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the future recreates itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.84,1:29:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The future constantly recreates itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.92,1:29:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it finds solutions for itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.80,1:29:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to find a solution to the year 2020 now, it doesn't have to yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.26,1:29:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year 2020, it'll come up with a bright solution to the problems of 2020.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.64,1:29:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.64,1:29:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Malthus's prediction that the world could only hold so many million people and then
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.66,1:29:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they would begin to starve to death never came true.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.03,1:29:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is productivity per acre has quadrupled, in fact, I think it's gone up like tenfold.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.95,1:29:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So although the population may double, our agricultural productivity has gone up to such
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.51,1:29:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,an extent that the government pays us to not till millions of acres.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.17,1:29:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get rich is to own millions of acres and do nothing with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.57,1:30:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the government will hand you all kinds of money, because there's too much food.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.80,1:30:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So our problem is we have too much food.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.76,1:30:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So Malthus was totally wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.22,1:30:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the thinkingness of Malthus-type people, you know, reemerges constantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.38,1:30:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees, you know, the negative potentiality of everything and then projects that and recreates.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.50,1:30:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And creates negativity for us to live with.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.28,1:30:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the thought that nothing is possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.82,1:30:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is impossible, which was expressed by Christopher Reeves as a very correct thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.76,1:30:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,irrespective of his politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.50,1:30:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.74,1:30:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So what seems impossible is an artifact of positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.84,1:30:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And when one transcends that, the answer is standing there clearly and obviously.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.82,1:30:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no problem that mankind has that the answer doesn't already exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.42,1:31:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And what would you reiterate?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.96,1:31:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.10,1:31:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you anticipate the collective level of human consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.60,1:31:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be coming up?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.10,1:31:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.10,1:31:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It could stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.10,1:31:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I say it was?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.10,1:31:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,204, 207?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.10,1:31:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the last time I calibrated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.66,1:31:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess would be that it'll probably stabilize there for a number of centuries.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.82,1:31:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it will, like a lion getting ready for a leap, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.29,1:31:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The lion looks like he's not moving, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.67,1:31:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.67,1:31:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He crouches.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.67,1:31:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like he's not moving, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.67,1:31:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, then when the lion leaps, now he's moving.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.67,1:31:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.67,1:31:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He was moving already because he has to gather himself up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.67,1:31:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.67,1:31:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the leap is only the end result of what's happened already.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.77,1:31:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great lion of society will again go into a crouch and begin to build up its power
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.33,1:31:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and strength, and it'll leap again.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.67,1:31:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.67,1:32:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll continue to leap.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.67,1:32:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.76,1:32:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the evolution of mankind will continue to leap.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.49,1:32:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.49,1:32:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once you're over 200, you're into the level of courage and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.49,1:32:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, once you're into courage and integrity, the answers to everything from that point
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.23,1:32:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are discoverable.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.31,1:32:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're below 200, you can't find the answer to anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.47,1:32:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're over 200, it's only a matter of time before you find the answer to everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.40,1:32:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.56,1:32:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.56,1:32:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When your goal is only over 200, you have courage and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.72,1:32:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage and integrity will lead you to the fact that love solves about 99% of human problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.66,1:32:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you're not at love yet, you discover that love has the power to heal.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.25,1:32:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.92,1:32:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.92,1:32:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.92,1:32:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.92,1:32:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.92,1:32:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.92,1:32:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.92,1:32:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.92,1:32:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.92,1:32:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.92,1:32:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.92,1:33:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.92,1:33:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
